{{Use Indian English|date=December 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=December 2014}} {{Infobox company | name = 4 Lions Films | image =4 Lions Films Logo.png | parent = | foundation = {{Start date|2008}} | founders = [[Gul Khan (producer)|Gul Khan]] | location_country = [[Mumbai]], [[India]] | key_people = {{Plainlist| * Gul Khan * Gorky M * Nissar Parvez * Karishma Jain }} | num_employees = 200 | industry = Entertainment | products = Television programs | revenue = | operating_income = | homepage = {{URL|www.4lionsfilms.com}} }}
'''4 Lions Films''' is a production house based in [[Mumbai]], [[India]]. Founded in 2008, its primary focus is youth-oriented and general entertainment shows.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-08-22/tv/33321136_1_tv-content-reality-show-internet-service-providers|title=Internet helps TV shows gain popularity|work=The Times of India}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mid-day.com/entertainment/2011/sep/090911-TV-soap-Geet-Gurmeet-Chaudhary-rumours.htm|title=Popular TV soap 'Geet' might go off air...|work=mid-day.com}}</ref>
==Operations== The house is based in [[Mumbai]] and it has made a range of television shows for [[Zee TV]], [[Channel V India|Channel V]], [[StarPlus]], [[Sony TV]]. Before the production house was created, many of its notable people had already worked together on youth shows such as ''[[Miley Jab Hum Tum]]'' and ''[[Dill Mill Gayye]]''. They also produces successful shows like ''[[Geet... Hui Sabse Parayi]]'', ''[[Iss Pyaar Ko Kya Naam Doon? (2011 TV series)|Iss Pyaar Ko Kya Naam Doon?]]'', ''[[Humse Hai Liife]]'', ''[[Qubool Hai]]'', ''[[Ishqbaaaz]].'' ''[[Kullfi Kumarr Bajewala]]'' and ''[[Nazar (TV series)|Nazar]]''.
