{{Infobox video game | title = Armillo | italic title = yes | state = expanded | image = File:Armillo.jpg | caption = Artwork released for the game. | developer = Fuzzy Wuzzy Games | publisher = Fuzzy Wuzzy Games | series = | engine = [[Unity (game engine)|Unity 4]] | platforms = [[Wii U]] | released = {{vgrelease|EU|July 3, 2014<ref name="release" />}} {{vgrelease|NA|July 3, 2014<ref name="release" />}}{{vgrelease|JP|October 22, 2014}} | genre = [[Action video game|Action]], [[platform video game|platform]], [[puzzle video game|puzzle]] | modes = [[Single-player video game|Single-player]] | director = | producer = | designer = | programmer = | artist = | writer = | composer = }}
'''''Armillo''''' is a 3D action puzzle platformer developed by Fuzzy Wuzzy Games. It was released on July 3, 2014 for the [[Wii U]] on the [[Nintendo eShop]].<ref name="release">{{cite web|url=http://www.gonintendo.com/s/223775-armillo-delayed-to-may-12th |title=Armillo delayed to May 12th |last=Cassidy |first=Kevin |publisher=GoNintendo |date=March 7, 2014 |accessdate=June 13, 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140308064636/http://www.gonintendo.com/s/223775-armillo-delayed-to-may-12th |archivedate=March 8, 2014 }}</ref>
== Gameplay == {{expand section|date=July 2014}}
''Armillo'' is an [[action game|action]] [[platform game]] in which the playable character, an [[armadillo]] named Armillo, rolls around a 3D space. He has the ability to perform three primary actions: roll, jump, and boost. The game is designed around the concept of an [[obstacle course]], so the player is constantly being presented to various new [[puzzle video game|puzzle]]s, mechanics and challenges.
Gameplay has been likened to other games such as the [[Sonic the Hedgehog|''Sonic the Hedgehog'' series]], [[Super Mario Galaxy]], and the ''[[Super Monkey Ball]]'' series.<ref name="destruct" /><ref name="independent" /> Players primarily progress through levels by rolling Armillo and have the option to utilize the tilt controls of the Wii U's GamePad to do so. Armillo is aided in his quest through special abilities and power-ups such as a size boost and the Critter gun which fires the [[non-playable characters|non-playable]] Critters at Armillo's enemies.<ref name="NWR" />
While the majority of the game takes place in a 3D world, there are unlockable 2D bonus stages in every single non-boss level.<ref name="NinLife" /> Purchasable upgrades, obtained using blue orbs collected in levels, also enable optional backtracking<ref name="NinLife" /> of previously completed levels.
== Development == {{expand section|date=July 2014}} Armillo was developed by Fuzzy Wuzzy Games for the Wii U, and is distributed on the Nintendo eShop. The game will be a timed exclusive on the platform, as it is scheduled to be released on other platforms in the future.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiedb.com/games/armillo-the-parallel-universe-mystery/news/armillo-is-coming-to-the-wii-u-eshop|title=Armillo is coming to the Wii U eShop!|author=knightSquared|publisher=Fuzzy Wuzzy Games|date=January 21, 2013|accessdate=January 21, 2013}}</ref> The decision was made in honor of [[Nintendo]]'s recent support for [[Independent video game development|independent developers]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nintendolife.com/news/2013/08/armillo_targets_q1_2014_release_on_the_wii_u_eshop_and_will_be_a_timed_exclusive|title=Armillo Targets Q1 2014 Release on the Wii U eShop and Will be a Timed Exclusive|last=Whitehead|first=Thomas|publisher=Nintendo Life|date=August 29, 2013|accessdate=August 29, 2013}}</ref> {{-}}
