}}'''Franz Czeisler''', also known as '''The Great Tihany''', was a Hungarian circus impresario and illusionist.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/obituaries/2016/04/05/franz-czeisler-circus-impresario---obituary/|title=Franz Czeisler, circus impresario - obituary|last=|first=|date=5 April 2015|website=The Telegraph|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref>

Czeisler got his first job in the circus at the age of 12, feeding the animals.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hungarianfreepress.com/2016/03/07/circus-legend-franz-czeisler-died-in-las-vegas-he-survived-horthys-henchmen/|title=Circus legend Franz Czeisler died in Las Vegas – he survived Horthy’s henchmen|last1=Lázár|first1=György|date=March 7, 2016|website=Hungarian Free Press}}</ref>

In 1953, he travelled to Brazil with his wife and son and purchased a [[Big top (circus)|big top]], which he used to start a circus.<ref name=":0" /> This eventually became the Circus Tihany, named after a town on [[Lake Balaton]], Hungary. The Circus Tihany toured every country in Central and South America for over 40 years.

